      "content": "Acetaminophen is the only pain reliever you can take, but you must strictly limit it to 2,000mg per day, and only for a short duration. Even with this limit, you should avoid it if you have any existing liver issues or if you are taking other medications that affect liver enzymes. If the headache persists, you must seek immediate medical attention because it could be a sign of a serious complication like a stroke or intracranial hemorrhage. Do not wait for the hospital to arrive; call emergency services now.",
